    "Html": "<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Hi Ben,</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Yes, Prism v2 is compatible with SL3!</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Please keep in mind that as Silverlight 3 is in beta version, it is not officially supported. However, features that previously existed in Silverlight 2 should work with Prism-v2 &amp; Silverlight 3. New features might not work<span style=\"color:#1f497d\"> </span><span style=\"\">out-of-the-box</span>.<span style=\"color:#1f497d\"> </span>&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">For instance Silverlight 3 navigation with </span><a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dd458946.aspx\"><span style=\"font-size:small;color:#0000ff;font-family:Calibri\">Remote Modularity</span></a><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\"> does not work. You can read more about that below:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt 34.8pt;text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font:7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/mconverti/2009/04/12/how-to-integrate-a-prism-v2-application-with-the-silverlight-3-navigation-framework/\"><span style=\"font-size:small;color:#0000ff;font-family:Calibri\">How To: Integrate a Prism v2 application with the Silverlight 3 Navigation Framework</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt 34.8pt;text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font:7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://compositewpf.codeplex.com/Thread/View.aspx?ThreadId=51053\"><span style=\"font-size:small;color:#0000ff;font-family:Calibri\">Prism 2 &amp; Silverlight 3 Beta Navigation</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -1.2pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">On the other side, I created a sample application that used a Silverlight 3 Data Form and </span><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/jdominguez/2008/08/icommand-for-silverlight-with-attached-behaviors/\"><span style=\"font-size:small;color:#0000ff;font-family:Calibri\">added a command with an attached behavior</span></a><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\"> to it:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt 34.8pt;text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font:7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman/2009/04/18/commands-with-attached-behavior-for-silverlight-3-dataform/\"><span style=\"font-size:small;color:#0000ff;font-family:Calibri\">Commands with Attached Behavior for Silverlight 3 DataForm</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Please let me know if this helps.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -0.6pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -0.6pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Damian Schenkelman</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -0.6pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff\">http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman</span></a></span></p>",
